				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">does vbl_clear_time.nes pass on an nes ? if so then it should also pass on an emu too ? if fx3 is failing that test then his emu doing something different from the nes ?</div>
<br />Good question. It does pass on a NES. However, like any test, it can fail for reasons other than what it's testing (for example, errors in CPU instruction emulation could always cause problems). Compared to the other VBL timing test, it can fail for more unrelated reasons, and it doesn't even test timing to an accuracy of 1/3 PPU clock. As I wrote more test ROMs, I learn more techniques for making them more focused on testing as little as possible beyond the target behavior.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

